cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper also involves the study of interference channels, which can be categorized under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). The use of state sequences in the channel also suggests a possible categorization under cs.SI (signal processing). The study of Gaussian channels and their capacity region can be categorized under cs.MM (machine learning) or cs.LG (learning).
